<bug>
    <id>98160</id>
    <title>Images are not shown in a WRITER document</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">User-Agent:       Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.3; WOW64; rv:44.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/44.0
Build Identifier: LibreOffice 5.1.0.3</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">If I insert an image with copy/paste into a new WRITER document then it is not shown.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">I see only an empty frame with "Image1".</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">If I print it or only open the Print Preview then the image is shown.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.4">After saving the file the thumbnail in the list of recent used documents shows the image correctly.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.5">This bug does not happen with LO 5.0.3 (previous installation).</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">This bug also happens with previous in LO 5.0.3 saved files.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Reproducible: Always</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.2">1 Open a new document in WRITER</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.3">2 Paste an image (e.g. from MS Paint) into the document</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.4">Result: You see only an empty frame, but no image.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">3 Go to FILE -&gt; PRINT</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.2">Result: In the thumbnail the image is shown correctly.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="7">
            <sentence id="7.1">4 Go to FILE -&gt; EXPORT AS PDF and save it as a PDF</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.2">Result: The image is shown correctly in the PDF.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="8">
            <sentence id="8.1">5 Go to FILE -&gt; SAVE AS and save the file</sentence>
            <sentence id="8.2">6 Close the file</sentence>
            <sentence id="8.3">7 Take a look at the thumbnails of recent used documents</sentence>
            <sentence id="8.4">Result: The image is shown correctly in the thumbnail</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="9">
            <sentence id="9.1">Actual Results:  
Images are not shown.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="10">
            <sentence id="10.1">Expected Results:  
Images are shown correctly.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
